snippet.textDisplay:
The zoom issues seem a little exaggerated. Like the Windows issue is that zoom converts UNC paths to links (aka. the exact same thing Outlook, Mail app, Word, OneNote, and basically everything does). The real flaw is that Windows Explorer (which is where that UNC link opens) provides your credentials to the server automatically. Trying to paint it as a zoom bug would be like calling a browser flaw a zoom bug because zoom was used to send the URL that brings you to the malicious site where the chrome bug is being exploited.


I feel like that is a great example of someone doing mental gymnastics to blame an unrelated issue on zoom to be able to cash in on the clickbait goldmine.
